    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nno, vim 8.2\n\n### Feature description\n\nThe only reason is that `all` dose not alway allow the cursor to go onemore.\r\nThis happens when a line is perfectly filed with characters, \r\nand the cursor goes onemore in that line,\r\nin which case the cursor would warp to the next line if `onemore` is set.\r\n\r\nFysical example:\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:set virtualedit=onemore\r\n\"=repeat('a',&columns)<CR>pl\r\n```",
